on%20away%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-sniper-in-ukraine-prefer-soviet-rifles-easier-get-bullets-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKalashnikov%20rifles%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20switch%20was%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20problem%20for%20many%20of%20his%20fellow%20soldiers%20at%20first.%20The%20Ukrainians%20weren't%20used%20to%20the%20M4%2C%20so%20they%20had%20to%20overcome%20some%20psychological%20barriers%20and%20past%20habits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20when%20a%20rifle%20shows%20results%2C%20it%20quickly%20changes%20your%20mind%20to%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20holding%20an%20AK-47%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20Kurakhove%20in%20December%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d1ad5d585f1dff88b1e4f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20holding%20an%20AK-47%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20Kurakhove%20in%20December%202024.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Diego%20Herrera%20Carcedo%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20M4%20carbine%20is%20a%20widely%20popular%20weapon%20developed%20in%20the%201980s%20by%20the%20American%20gun%20maker%20Colt's%20Manufacturing%20Company.%20It's%20a%20shorter%20version%20of%20the%20M16%20used%20by%20the%20US%20military%20and%20dozens%20of%20other%20countries%2C%20and%20it%20fires%205.56%C3%9745%20mm%20NATO%20rounds.%20This%20is%20a%20change%20from%20the%20Soviet%20Kalashnikovs%2C%20also%20widely%20used%2C%20which%20fire%207.62x39%20mm%20ammunition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Kalashnikov%2C%20represented%20by%20firearms%20like%20the%20AK-47%20and%20AK-74%2C%20is%20a%20very%20recognizable%20collection%20of%20assault%20rifles%20that%20were%20originally%20designed%20and%20produced%20in%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%20Given%20Ukraine's%20history%20with%20Soviet%20weaponry%2C%20the%20country%20is%20more%20accustomed%20to%20these%20rifles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20issues%20during%20the%20transition%2C%20Harley%20said%2C%20was%20that%20the%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20didn't%20receive%20enough%20M4%20bullets%20%E2%80%94%20only%20around%20100%20per%20soldier%20each%20day%20%E2%80%94%20for%20training%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20war.%20They%20did%2C%20however%2C%20have%20plenty%20of%20rounds%20for%20the%20Kalashnikovs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20American%20sniper%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-sniper-in-ukraine-prefer-soviet-rifles-easier-get-bullets-2024-4%3FIR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprefers%20the%20Soviet%20weapons%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20the%20ammunition%20is%20easier%20to%20come%20by.%20The%20Ukrainians%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20it%2C%20and%20they%20can%20always%20take%20bullets%20off%20the%20Russians%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20don't%20train%20well%2C%20it's%20difficult%20for%20you%20in%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20Harley%20said.%20%26quot%3BOf%20course%2C%20in%20operations%2C%20no%20one%20limited%20us%20to%20ammunition%2C%20and%20we%20had%20as%20much%20ammunition%20as%20we%20wanted.%20But%20it%20was%20during%20training%20that%2C%20at%20first%2C%20we%20did%20not%20have%20enough%20ammunition%20to%20prepare%20properly%20and%20raise%20our%20hits%20to%20the%20level%20required.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarley%20said%20that%20once%20the%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20started%20using%20the%20M4%20in%20combat%20missions%2C%20they%20became%20comfortable%20with%20the%20rifles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226706%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20US%20Army%20Reserve%20drill%20sergeant%20fires%20an%20M4%20rifle%20at%20a%20training%20range%20in%20Germany%20in%20February%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d1add5585f1dff88b1e50e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224471%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Army%20Reserve%20drill%20sergeant%20fires%20an%20M4%20rifle%20at%20a%20training%20range%20in%20Germany%20in%20February%202024.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Sgt.%201st%20Class%20Kevin%20A.%20D.%20Spence%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20ammunition%20and%20psychological%20barriers%2C%20the%20upgrade%20had%20only%20advantages.%20They%20eventually%20received%20enough%20bullets%20for%20extensive%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20this%20situation%20has%20changed%2C%20we%20have%20everything%20available%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI%20earlier%20this%20month.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20raised%20our%20level%20of%20proficiency%20with%20this%20weapon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20switch%20from%20the%20Kalashnikovs%20to%20the%20M4%20is%20one%20of%20many%20examples%20where%2C%20after%20Russia%20launched%20its%20full-scale%20invasion%2C%20Ukrainian%20troops%20traded%20Soviet-designed%20weaponry%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabrams-bradleys-built-cold-war-battle-with-soviets-fight-russia-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWestern-made%20combat%20equipment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20are%20fighting%20in%20American%20Bradley%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicles%20instead%20of%20BMPs%2C%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20instead%20of%20old%20MiGs%20and%20Sukhois%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-abrams-tank-problem-going-to-get-worse-trump-administration-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAbrams%20tanks%3C%2Fa%3E%20instead%20of%20T-72%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarley%20said%20that%20later%20in%20the%20war%2C%20the%20SOF%20received%20and%20started%20using%20the%20DDM4%20rifle%2C%20which%20is%20similar%20to%20the%20M4A1.%20He%20said%20this%20weapon%20combines%20some%20of%20the%20characteristics%20of%20an%20assault%20rifle%20and%20a%20sniper%20rifle%2C%20allowing%20for%20flexibility%20in%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Russia%20invaded%2C%20Ukraine's%20Western%20backers%20have%20given%20it%20weapons%20to%20boost%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzelenskyy-advisor-patriots-weapon-concern-over-trump-aid-cuts-ukraine-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefensive%20capabilities%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Beyond%20tanks%2C%20armored%20vehicles%2C%20and%20fighters%2C%20the%20war-torn%20country%20has%20also%20received%20artillery%2C%20air%20defenses%2C%20and%20long-range%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20hasn't%20always%20been%20the%20smoothest%20process%2C%20with%20Western%20indecision%20and%20delays%20at%20times%20causing%20Ukraine%20to%20miss%20critical%20windows%20of%20opportunity.%20It%20continues%20to%20be%20a%20challenge%20even%20now%20as%20Ukraine%20is%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-and-putin-may-have-a-deal-but-its-a-long-way-ukraine-wars-end-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enegotiations%20to%20potentially%20end%20the%20war%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fupgrading-soviet-era-kalashnikovs-for-american-m4s-hard-for-ukrainians-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742553121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d1ae33b8b41a9673fa66fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fupgrading-soviet-era-kalashnikovs-for-american-m4s-hard-for-ukrainians-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20soldier%20in%20Ukraine's%20Special%20Operations%20Forces%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20upgrade%20was%20an%20adjustment%20for%20some%2C%20but%20they%20got%20the%20hang%20of%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jepstein%40businessinsider.com%20(Jake%20Epstein)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fupgrading-soviet-era-kalashnikovs-for-american-m4s-har