2C%20and%20innovation%20organization.%20Mattmann%20spent%20nearly%2024%20years%20at%20NASA%20before%20joining%20UCLA%20in%20June%202024%20as%20chief%20data%20and%20artificial%20intelligence%20officer.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20started%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-science-scientists-salaries-talent-shortage-ocodo-airbnb-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20science%3C%2Fa%3E%20long%20before%20it%20was%20even%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bdata%20science.%26quot%3B%20When%20I%20studied%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%20from%201998%20to%202007%2C%20I%20worked%20on%20data%20architecture%2C%20data%20engineering%2C%20databases%2C%20and%20data%20systems.%20My%20biggest%20interest%20was%20how%20they%20were%20all%20interconnected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20working%20at%20NASA%20as%20an%20academic%20part-time%20employee%20in%20January%202001.%20Soon%20after%2C%20I%20was%20hired%20full%20time%20as%20a%20data%20engineer%20and%20software%20engineer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20moved%20up%20at%20NASA's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-jet-propulsion-laboratory-tour-2016-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJet%20Propulsion%20Laboratory%20(JPL)%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20working%20on%20missions%2C%20and%20had%20my%20big%20break%20while%20working%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpl.nasa.gov%2Fmissions%2Forbiting-carbon-observatory-oco%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOrbiting%20Carbon%20Observatory%20Mission%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20next-generation%20earth%20science%20instrument.%20I%20became%20JPL's%20chief%20technology%20and%20innovation%20officer%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ba4b190b-a301-45d9-8c01-8b7f88f52e2d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere%20are%20the%205%20things%20I'd%20warn%20anyone%20who%20wants%20to%20get%20into%20data%20science%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f022cdee-182e-49dd-a559-46a2a3573db6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Study%20the%20discipline%20or%20data%20field%20that%20you'll%20be%20working%20in.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20entered%20the%20industry%2C%20I%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20training%20in%20software%20development%20and%20engineering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20saw%20that%20people%20coming%20out%20with%20data%20degrees%20were%20more%20effective%20as%20data%20scientists%20than%20the%20software%20developers%20who%20took%20years%20just%20to%20learn%20what%20latitude%20and%20longitude%20were%3B%20teaching%20an%20earth%20scientist%20Python%20was%20more%20effective%20than%20teaching%20a%20software%20engineering%20Ph.D.%20earth%20science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%2C%20I%20wish%20my%20first%20five%20years%20were%20spent%20learning%20earth%20science%2C%20planetary%20science%2C%20and%20more%20math%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcomputer-science-major-myth-job-security-money-salary-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erather%20than%20software%20development%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20engineering%2C%20which%20I%20could've%20picked%20up%20in%20greater%20detail%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recommend%20that%20folks%20get%20a%20discipline%20science%20degree%20rather%20than%20a%20computer%20or%20software%20degree.%20AI%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-ladder-software-engineers-collapsing-ai-google-meta-coding-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoming%20for%20your%20software%20engineering%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20it%20isn't%20the%20best%20at%20discipline%20sciences.%20Getting%20a%20degree%20in%20those%20areas%20will%20allow%20you%20to%20have%20a%20lengthier%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dc77cba8-7f7d-419d-a7e4-e8dc338199f2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Early%20in%20your%20career%2C%20get%20some%20experience%20with%20data%20science%20and%20AI%20operations.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESomeone%20can%20enter%20this%20field%20in%20two%20main%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20is%20by%20doing%20something%20interesting%20with%20open-source%20tools%20and%20data%20and%20then%20putting%20it%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgithub%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyour%20GitHub%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20others%20to%20review%20and%20see%2C%20which%20proves%20you%20can%20do%20a%20real-world%20problem.%20Kaggle%20has%20many%20challenges%20like%20this%20where%20you%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-career-change-machine-learning-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompete%20against%20others%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20is%20by%20working%20or%20studying%20under%20a%20mentor%20or%20doing%20an%20internship%2C%20where%20you%20make%20a%20publicly%20reviewable%20contribution%20to%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20the%20sweet%20spot%20is%20to%20carefully%20navigate%20both%20data%20research%20and%20operations%3B%20don't%20just%20hide%20in%20the%20research%20domain%3B%20instead%2C%20actually%20learn%20the%20software%20engineering%20necessary%20to%20deliver%20the%20application%20of%20research%2C%20data%2C%20and%20AI%20to%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20find%20operations%20to%20be%20a%20much%20more%20rewarding%20and%20less%20cutthroat%20field%20than%20research%20and%20the%20science%20publishing%20community%20and%20pipeline.%20My%20work%20in%20operations%20has%20included%20everything%20from%20NASA%20missions%20focused%20on%20big%20data%20for%20earth%20science%2C%20to%20software%20like%20Apache%20Hadoop%20and%20Apache%20Tika%2C%20which%20are%20used%20around%20the%20world%20by%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20people%20and%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22488a83f8-c5a5-46c8-b945-39ebc69e5194%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20To%20succeed%20in%20data%20science%2C%20prepare%20to%20be%20considered%20%26quot%3Bthe%20help%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20the%20person%20driving%20the%20domain.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20challenges%20were%20preparing%20myself%20not%20to%20be%20in%20the%20lead%2C%20spending%20time%20working%20in%20the%20background%20on%20data%20analysis%2C%20and%20having%20others%20get%20most%20of%20the%20credit%20for%20the%20work%20I%20enabled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20often%20say%20I'm%20a%20%26quot%3Blittle%20s%26quot%3B%20scientist%2C%20not%20a%20%26quot%3Bbig%20S%26quot%3B%20scientist%20like%20the%20others%20%E2%80%94%20mostly%20because%20I%20was%20made%20to%20feel%20that%20way.%20I%20was%20constantly%20put%20as%20the%20second%20or%20last%20author%20on%20papers%20that%20I%20was%20the%20largest%20contributor%20to%2C%20so%20the%20earth%20or%20planetary%20scientist%20could%20get%20their%20first%20author%20paper%20at%20a%20major%20conference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20an%20%26quot%3Bassistant%26quot%3B%20in%20many%20cases%20to%20the%20actual%20discipline%20scientist%20that%20you're%20preparing%2C%20analyzing%2C%20and%20working%20on%20the%20data%20for.%20You're%20also%20now%20the%20%26quot%3Bhelp%26quot%3B%20for%20fueling%20AI%2C%20which%20is%20heavily%20data-dependent%2C%20so%20you%20have%20to%20humble%20yourself%20greatly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20have%20a%20manager%20you%20really%20trust%2C%20you%20can%20try%20to%20move%20into%20data%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-researcher-soft-skills-valuable-ai-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20analytics%2C%20so%20you%20can%20share%20the%20credit%20without%20being%20worried%20about%20getting%20pushed%20to%20the%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2241346a51-8103-4471-bf76-2a710476ee76%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Build%20a%20network%20of%20friends%20to%20support%20you%20through%20your%20data%20science%20and%20AI%20journey.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ECommunity%20in%20data%20science%20is%20so%20important.%20You%20need%20folks%20around%20you%20to%20lift%20you%20up%20and%20be%20interested%20in